            <grade>0</grade>
            <score>0</score>
            <flags>0</flags>
            <timecreated>1469463873</timecreated>
            <timemodified>0</timemodified>
            <answer_text>We don't have enough information.</answer_text>
            <response>We do have enough information to conclude which ant travels further.  Both ants complete a "trip around the circle" in the same amount of time (the same amount of time it takes for the turntable to go around once).  Ant B travels further in that time because it is going around a larger circle, so it is going faster.  We can't *calculate* their speeds with the information given but we certainly know which is going faster.</response>
